Title: Warner Bros. Studio during the Conference of Studio Unions strike, Los Angeles, 1945
Description.note: Workers on strike outside of the Warner Brothers studio during the CSU strike. A car is overturned in the middle of the street.|~|The Conference of Studio Unions strike was against all Hollywood studios. The CSU strike began in March 1945 and was around the six month mark when it turned violent on October 5, 1945, known as Hollywood Black Friday. National exposure of this violence forced negotiations between studios and the CSU. Negotiation ended the strike about a month later, but CSU didn't last much longer and was eventually disbanded and absorbed by rival union IATSE.
Description.fundingNote: Access to this collection is generously supported by Haynes Foundation funds.

Title: Outdoor nursing class for deaf students at Los Angeles Trade Technical College, Los Angeles, 1976

Trade Tech: From left, assistant instructor Katherine Carlson, Charlotte Friedman, Adrianne Riley, Koni Battad, Lana Swearington, Genevieve Baldwin, instructor Ronnie Fisher and interpretor Darryl Allen.
